    "description": "Takeda iP Holdings Co.,Ltd. engages in information and communication, solutions sales, semiconductor-related masks, and real estate leasing businesses in Japan. The company is involved in the real estate rental and management operation; planning, design, printing, and logistics services for various printed materials primarily commercial printing; design of semiconductor parts; manufacture and sale of jigs and tools related to semiconductor parts; and sale of machinery and equipment. It also engages in the repair, sale, and leasing of machinery and equipment for printing, bookbinding, and paper container manufacturing. The company was formerly known as Takeda Printing Co., Ltd. and changed its name to Takeda iP Holdings Co.,Ltd. in April 2023. Takeda iP Holdings Co.,Ltd. was founded in 1924 and is headquartered in Nagoya, Japan."
